718855f-a.text:
Church Street (elevated line thereon), east side, north from Cortlandt Street (station) to Fulton Street and showing an excavation where the former 15-story Havemeyer Building stood. The East River Savings Bank will erect a 1-story banking structure on this site. The new 2-story building seen north of same,is occupied as a retail store by
F. W. Woolworth & Co.
March 5, 1934.
P. L. Sperr.
